The question to Obama, however, is whether his commitment to bilingual training, which focuses on teaching in languages other than English, contradicts his interest in reducing the distance in schooling.
Take, for example, Sixth Street Prep, a primary school in eastern Los Angeles.
The majority of students are Hispanic and come from low-income families.
