I mean not those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
If it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be scared, but in reality it has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and young people.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon may occur occasionally (one time in life, for example, during the high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no reason to cause this phenomenon.
Often, relationships with other phenomena are sought in sleep, such as nightmares, panic at night, enuresis noctura (bedding at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for that.
As we mentioned earlier, it may be due to very high fiber, stress situations or overload.
Anyway, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that you are speaking quietly in individual words, whispering or it can be quite an opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended that the child be observed and consulted with a specialist to see if there is a problem that causes fear and thus arises.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with the sleep apnoea or with the stress).
What you can do is to carry out a series of simple prevention measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet play for the child and avoid stressful television programs that are terrible and a little too wild.
For the nervous children who are recommended for relaxation, relaxation methods can be used to help them get a certain inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep quietly.
Once speaking in sleep, try to maintain calm.
Remember that it is harmless for the child and the next day it will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, for the child is unconscious, so you will tear it out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, it sleeps, so it rests.
Remember, if it appears frightened after a few appearances, it is recommended to be advised or to find out the reason the child is afraid.
If they understand what it says (which is not so usual), the child does not put pressure on them to carry out a hearing and to obtain more information.
Thus you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child sleeps, it is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Moreover, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams and why it says so, therefore be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Maybe it doesn't tell the child that you hear that at night and know his secrets.
Not even as a joke.
That's what causes a lot of fear.
So, don't worry, it's nothing bad, it's a moment that takes only a few minutes.
